FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1772048439
OL,3,CAll schools must provide SEN places
OL,4,Camid rising demand says Education
OL,5,CMinister
OL,7,FOn Monday, UK Education Secretary
OL,8,FBridget Phillipson set out major
OL,9,Freforms to the special educational
OL,10,Fneeds and disabilities (SEND) system,
OL,11,Fsaying the government will "take away
OL,12,Fthat fight that so many parents" often
OL,13,Fface in accessing legally-guaranteed
OL,14,Fsupport.
OL,16,FIn September 2025, 34,011 pupils in
OL,17,FNorthern Ireland had a statement of
OL,18,FSEND, an increase of 85% in 10 years,
OL,19,Faccording to the Education Authority
OL,20,F(EA).
OL,26,@sD@\OUtD@`O]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/8
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1772048439
OL,3,CAll schools must provide SEN places
OL,4,Camid rising demand says Education
OL,5,CMinister
OL,7,FIn his letter to principals, Mr Givan
OL,8,Facknowledged "the need for all types
OL,9,Fof SEN provision has grown
OL,10,Fexponentially in recent years and is
OL,11,Fprojected to continue to rise, even
OL,12,Fwith a predicted decline in the
OL,13,Foverall school age population".
OL,15,FHe added: "All schools have a role to
OL,16,Fplay in meeting the needs of this
OL,17,Fchanging demographic.
OL,26,@pD@NOUuD@^O]wD@KOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/8
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1772048439
OL,3,CAll schools must provide SEN places
OL,4,Camid rising demand says Education
OL,5,CMinister
OL,7,F"To meet future demand and ensure that
OL,8,Fchildren do not have to travel
OL,9,Funacceptably long distances to access
OL,10,Fappropriate placements, I am now
OL,11,Frequiring all mainstream schools which
OL,12,Fthe EA considers suitable to
OL,13,Ffacilitate specialist provision to
OL,14,Fengage constructively with them to put
OL,15,Fit in place.
OL,26,@oD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/8
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1772048439
OL,3,CAll schools must provide SEN places
OL,4,Camid rising demand says Education
OL,5,CMinister
OL,7,F"The policy objective is to ensure
OL,8,Fchildren and young people with a
OL,9,Fstatement of SEN have access to an
OL,10,Fappropriate specialist placement in
OL,11,Ftheir local community, where possible,
OL,12,Fand educated alongside their friends
OL,13,Fand peers."
OL,15,FThe Education Minister paid tribute to
OL,16,Fschools that have established
OL,17,Fspecialist provision, but said he "had
OL,18,Fhoped that more would have done so,"
OL,19,Fadding: "A more direct approach is now
OL,20,Fconsidered necessary.
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@KO]yD@cOUzD@dO]{D@IOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/8
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1772048439
OL,3,CAll schools must provide SEN places
OL,4,Camid rising demand says Education
OL,5,CMinister
OL,7,F"The feedback I have received from
OL,8,Fthose schools which have already set
OL,9,Fup specialist provision has been
OL,10,Foverwhelmingly positive, however I
OL,11,Faccept that schools need to be
OL,12,Fadequately supported through this
OL,13,Fprocess."
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@IO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/8
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1772048439
OL,3,CAll schools must provide SEN places
OL,4,Camid rising demand says Education
OL,5,CMinister
OL,7,FMr Givan said the move did not stem
OL,8,Ffrom a desire to "transfer
OL,9,Fresponsibility for this issue to
OL,10,Fschools, but rather to ensure the
OL,11,Fsystem as a whole comes together in a
OL,12,Fmore collegiate and effective way to
OL,13,Fmeet the needs of some of the most
OL,14,Fvulnerable children in our society".
OL,16,FThe minister pledged that an enhanced
OL,17,Fsupport package from the EA would be
OL,18,Favailable to schools.
OL,20,FCatch up with the latest UTV Live on
OL,21,FITVX
OL,26,@pD@ROUvD@cO]
